# Local dev secrets/config must never be baked into a built image — Bun
# auto-loads .env files from its working directory at runtime with no
# explicit dotenv import needed, so a leaked .env here silently overrides
# whatever the deploy platform actually injects (this shipped NODE_ENV as
# "development" into what render.yaml declares a production service).
#
# Must be **/.env, not a bare .env: our Dockerfiles COPY named subdirectories
# (e.g. `COPY backend ./backend`) rather than the whole context, and verified
# empirically that an unanchored `.env` pattern does NOT reach into a
# subdirectory copied that way with this BuildKit version — only the `**/`
# form does. Don't "simplify" this back to a bare `.env`.
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

**/node_modules
**/.git
**/dist
**/*.log
